Philoosophical Stances:

realism        # view of a mind-independent existence of a thing
positivism     # Empiricism+. from David Hume, Augustus Comte, Popper.
naturalism     # all beings and events in the universe are natural, so is relevant to study scientifically. Generally not metaphysical.
materialism    # reducing the universe to physical facts and processes.
legalism       # (western meaning) strict adherence to the letter of the law.
interpretivism # law exists through the interpretations and aims of lawyers actions.
pragmatism     # meaning lies in its observable practical uses and consequences.
formalism      # rigourous adherence to recognized forms.
structuralism  # understanding elements by their relationship to a broader system.
constructivism # TODO


Liberalism       # John Locke. Replacing norms of hereditary privilege, state religion and monarchy with rights of the individual, consent of the governed. Political.
Neoliberalism    # conservative focus on free-market capitalism. Privatization, deregulation, globalization, free trade, monetarism, austerity. Political.
Conservatism     # seeks to preserve traditional institutions and practices. Supposedly for slow change. Political.
Libertarianism   # seeks to maximize 'liberty', by minimising the state's encroachment on individuals. Political.
Communitarianism # views individuals as existing and shaped within a broad community, Political.
individualism    # emphasises the independence and importance of an individual, over their connection to a community. Political.
Communism        # theoretical post-capitalist economic system with collective ownership of property Political.
Socialism        # focus on social ownership Political.
Fascism          # nationalist centralization of authority, capitalist economy with suppression of opposition, with racism. Political.
